WEBVTT

00:02.295 --> 00:04.251
MOHINDER:
Previously on Heroes.

00:04.505 --> 00:06.245
I think our only
real option at this point

00:06.340 --> 00:07.921
is to get the Unites States
Government involved.

00:08.009 --> 00:09.874
/ want to round them up
and put them in a facility

00:09.969 --> 00:11.630
where they won’t be
a danger to anyone.

00:11.721 --> 00:14.679
What would your hunter do
if he knew you were
one of them, too?

00:16.100 --> 00:18.682
Who are you?
And what do you want?

00:18.978 --> 00:20.843
I want you to
get in the van.

00:23.649 --> 00:27.688
(ALARM BEEPING)
PILOT: Mayday, mayday, mayday!
Den Mother 3-1 going down.

00:27.820 --> 00:29.026
Daphne!

00:29.113 --> 00:30.102
(GUN FIRES)

00:31.115 --> 00:32.651
Daphne!
MOHINDER: Matt!

00:33.409 --> 00:35.149
If you don't want
to see them punished,
what do you want?

00:35.244 --> 00:36.780
I want them to pay.

00:38.206 --> 00:39.992
What are you saying
to her, Nathan?

00:40.082 --> 00:42.869
You're telling her
that I'm unstable? Crazed?

00:43.628 --> 00:44.663
You look me up.

00:44.754 --> 00:46.460
It's over, Pete.
Give up.

00:46.964 --> 00:48.579
No, this is the beginning.

00:48.674 --> 00:49.925
(WHOOSHING)

00:51.219 --> 00:52.880
He's working for
a secret program,

00:52.970 --> 00:54.255
imprisoning people
with powers.

00:54.347 --> 00:56.679
MR. BENNET:
Has it ever occurred to you
that I don't have a choice?

00:56.766 --> 00:58.222
There is always a choice!

00:58.309 --> 00:59.890
...and they have made it
very clear to me

00:59.977 --> 01:02.719
that if I am not on board,
that Claire will be
on that list!

01:02.813 --> 01:05.646
Your mother wants me
to move out of the house
for a while.

01:07.985 --> 01:09.145
She's right.

01:16.994 --> 01:18.450
MOHINDER:
I don't like this, Matt.

01:18.537 --> 01:20.038
MATT: Well, you got
any better ideas?

01:20.122 --> 01:22.579
MOHINDER: It's a huge risk,
being out in the open.
We should be laying low.

01:22.667 --> 01:26.410
And what? What?
Run forever?

01:26.504 --> 01:29.211
I don't know.
Yeah. That's my point.

01:29.298 --> 01:33.337
We're being hunted,
and we have no idea
by who, how, why.

01:33.427 --> 01:35.258
Noah Bennet has
all the answers
that we're looking for.

01:35.346 --> 01:37.507
Hey, did you get it?
Yeah.

01:38.933 --> 01:41.640
Amobarbital.
One dose of this,
he's knocked out cold.

01:43.145 --> 01:44.521
What? What's wrong?

01:45.273 --> 01:47.514
Can't you just read his mind?
Get what we need that way?

01:47.608 --> 01:49.018
No. We've been over this.

01:49.110 --> 01:51.726
Noah is too well-trained,
and he's never off his guard.

01:51.821 --> 01:55.734
Guys, look, I was a cop.
You're a scientist. A nurse.

01:55.825 --> 01:58.111
We did nothing wrong,
and they turned us
into fugitives.

01:58.202 --> 02:00.784
But drugging
and kidnapping people?

02:00.871 --> 02:03.453
Look, I don't like it,
either, but this way,
it gives us answers.

02:03.541 --> 02:06.954
Yeah, straight up
interrogation isn't going
to work, not with Bennet.

02:07.044 --> 02:08.659
We need to get creative.

02:13.634 --> 02:15.010
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

02:26.230 --> 02:27.891
(SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

02:32.778 --> 02:34.564
Staying at the hotel?
Yeah.

02:39.493 --> 02:41.154
Just for a little while.

02:41.245 --> 02:45.409
I'm actually looking
for an apartment in town,
if you know of anything.

02:46.542 --> 02:47.657
No.

02:48.753 --> 02:50.334
Welcome to Costa Verde.

02:54.633 --> 02:56.419
(MUS/C D/STORTED)

03:22.995 --> 03:26.032
Well, it looks like
our friend here had
about three too many.

03:26.123 --> 03:28.284
Don't worry.
We'll get him home safe.

03:35.841 --> 03:37.001
PETER: Well?

03:38.594 --> 03:39.709
(PANTING)

03:39.804 --> 03:41.135
MATT: It's working.

03:43.641 --> 03:45.131
It's working.

04:07.164 --> 04:11.578
Ten people died last night
in Ohio when a house
spontaneously caught on fire.

04:11.669 --> 04:14.581
I'm thinking
we should investigate
sooner rather than later.

04:15.464 --> 04:17.841
It's over, Noah.
It's all over.

04:17.925 --> 04:20.416
Primatech may have burned
to the ground, but that
doesn't change anything.

04:20.511 --> 04:21.967
We have a lot
of work to do.

04:22.054 --> 04:25.217
Primatech should
have been shut down
a longtime ago.

04:25.307 --> 04:27.764
The Company had a good run,
but its time has passed.

04:27.852 --> 04:30.810
No. We got the job done.

04:30.896 --> 04:34.730
Yes, you certainly did,
and I appreciate it.

04:39.363 --> 04:41.103
What is this?

04:41.198 --> 04:45.316
For your years of service.
Pension. Severance.

04:46.162 --> 04:47.823
And this is from me.

04:59.967 --> 05:01.958
Why are you doing this?

05:03.053 --> 05:06.136
Bag and tag.
One of us,
one of them.

05:06.223 --> 05:10.182
It's an antiquated system
desperately trying
to remain relevant.

05:10.269 --> 05:12.601
So, we adapt
and we get it right.

05:12.688 --> 05:17.352
I don't think we can,
I don't think we should.
lam tired, Noah.

05:18.777 --> 05:20.813
l have told so many lies.

05:20.905 --> 05:25.194
Maybe it's not too late
to cobble my family
back together.

05:26.076 --> 05:29.864
But it's a good thing.
You get to go home,
to Claire.

05:29.955 --> 05:33.072
This is everything
you've ever fought for,
and you won.

05:40.424 --> 05:42.255
This is all I've ever known.

05:45.387 --> 05:47.844
What am I supposed
to do now?

05:47.932 --> 05:49.388
Take care of Claire.

05:50.768 --> 05:52.224
Take care of yourself.

06:07.117 --> 06:08.618
(EXHALES)

06:10.120 --> 06:14.534
All right. So, I'm gonna be
able to get to these memories
that we're looking for.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.991
I'm going to find out exactly
how this whole thing happened,

06:17.086 --> 06:19.077
who's behind it
and how they work.

06:19.171 --> 06:21.878
We're gonna find out
how to stop hiding
and start fighting back.

06:21.966 --> 06:24.207
And how far are you
willing to push?

06:24.301 --> 06:25.586
(GASPS)

06:25.678 --> 06:28.385
As far as I need to.

06:49.952 --> 06:51.613
This better be good.

06:51.704 --> 06:53.660
Face time at state dinners
is hard to come by.

06:53.789 --> 06:55.575
You heard from Bennet?
No. Why?

06:55.666 --> 06:57.702
He's off the grid,
going on three hours.

06:57.793 --> 06:59.909
Standing orders are
to check in after duty.
He didn't.

07:00.296 --> 07:04.335
What about Claire?
Is she okay?
Yes. Your daughter's fine.

07:04.425 --> 07:06.416
I want every inch
of surveillance
on Noah Bennet.

07:06.510 --> 07:08.876
Everywhere he's been,
everywhere he might go.

07:10.264 --> 07:11.754
You spying on
your own men?

07:11.849 --> 07:14.761
Nobody is above scrutiny,
myself included.

07:14.852 --> 07:17.468
You and Bennet,
you're both compromised.

07:17.563 --> 07:18.769
What's that supposed
to mean?

07:18.856 --> 07:20.437
Your brother, Peter,
your daughter, Claire...

07:20.524 --> 07:21.764
Peter gets treated
like everyone else.

07:21.859 --> 07:23.941
Yeah, and Claire
gets a free pass.

07:24.028 --> 07:26.770
That makes both
yours and Bennet's
choices tarnished.

07:31.327 --> 07:35.445
Are you spying on me?
You barely touched
your prime rib.

07:47.551 --> 07:48.586
Everything okay
out there?

07:48.677 --> 07:51.293
Yeah, it still feels
like we're sitting ducks
in here, come on.

07:51.388 --> 07:52.844
We can't rush
an interrogation.

07:52.931 --> 07:57.220
This isn't an interrogation.
lt's torture. You're straining
his entire system.

07:58.062 --> 08:00.178
(BOTH EXHALE SHARPLY)

08:00.272 --> 08:02.308
What, do you think
I'm hurting him on purpose?

08:02.399 --> 08:04.264
