22:12.248 --> 22:13.624
You think I don't
regret any of this!

22:13.708 --> 22:16.199
You were my friend!
You could have warned me!

22:16.294 --> 22:18.501
You could have
warned all of us!
I didn't know what to do.

22:18.630 --> 22:20.962
I didn't believe him!
Even after the plane,
the least you could...

22:21.049 --> 22:23.540
What? Told you that
I could've stopped
all of this,

22:23.635 --> 22:26.172
that I could have
maybe prevented
Daphne's death?

22:28.473 --> 22:32.307
If I had,
I'd probably be the one
tied up in that Chair.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.487
Come on!

22:48.451 --> 22:50.487
All right,
Check baCk there.
I got over here.

23:13.184 --> 23:14.424
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

23:20.650 --> 23:21.639
(GRUNTS)

23:28.199 --> 23:29.279
Hi.

23:33.746 --> 23:35.486
We got to hurry.
They found me,
they're gonna find us.

23:35.582 --> 23:38.915
We're gonna get all
the answers we're looking for,
without the drugs.

23:39.002 --> 23:41.334
I want him
to feel everything.

23:43.590 --> 23:44.955
MATT: How do we fight baCk?

23:45.049 --> 23:46.880
You always have a plan,
now you're gonna
share it with us.

23:46.968 --> 23:48.924
Listen to Peter,
get the hell out of here
while you still can.

23:49.012 --> 23:51.970
How much time
do you think you have,
Matt, before they find us?

23:52.056 --> 23:53.921
Maybe we should
just take what
Peter has and run.

23:54.017 --> 23:55.757
You don't get a vote!

23:55.893 --> 23:57.758
What are you
talking about?
Nothing!

23:57.854 --> 24:01.472
Mohinder knew
that we were gonna get
attacked by the government.

24:01.566 --> 24:02.772
Is that true?

24:02.859 --> 24:04.975
Bennet came to me, yes,
but I didn't believe him.

24:05.069 --> 24:07.230
He manipulated me before,
and I didn't think
I could trust him.

24:07.322 --> 24:08.937
Why didn't you
say something?

24:09.032 --> 24:11.148
As if any of you
would believe me,
after what I've done.

24:11.284 --> 24:12.615
Yeah, it's better
that we didn't.
PETER: Look, come on.

24:12.702 --> 24:14.533
You're a coward!
Can you get anything
more out of him?

24:14.621 --> 24:16.486
Yeah. I was just
about to do that.

24:19.000 --> 24:20.706
Who's the guy
you were taking
orders from?

24:20.793 --> 24:22.658
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

24:22.754 --> 24:24.995
Wait, wait. What guy?
I thought he was in Charge.

24:25.089 --> 24:27.205
Turns out he's still
middle management.

24:28.718 --> 24:30.629
Who is he?

24:31.512 --> 24:33.093
(GRUNTS) Who? Who?

24:33.181 --> 24:34.170
(GASPS)

24:53.951 --> 24:56.488
You.
Got a minute?

25:02.251 --> 25:04.287
I think we got off
on the wrong foot.

25:06.172 --> 25:07.673
l was hoping
we could talk.

25:07.757 --> 25:09.668
What are we gonna
talk about?

25:12.387 --> 25:14.628
We're gonna be
working together.

25:14.722 --> 25:17.259
I thought maybe it'd be
a good idea ifwe...

25:17.350 --> 25:20.217
What? Got to know
eaCh other better?

25:21.938 --> 25:24.145
...understood where
the other guy
was coming from.

25:24.273 --> 25:27.765
I already know where
you're coming from.
And where is that?

25:29.570 --> 25:31.652
You got a family at home.

25:32.448 --> 25:37.408
A wife, a boy,
and your daughter,
Claire, right?

25:39.080 --> 25:43.369
She's the speCial one
with a soft spot in
the Senator's soft heart.

25:43.876 --> 25:45.127
That's right.

25:46.295 --> 25:50.334
You're a dime a dozen,
and 11 out of 12
are unreliable.

25:50.425 --> 25:52.086
(CHUCKUNG)

25:52.176 --> 25:56.294
You don't know anything
about me. That's the whole
point of this, you know?

25:57.473 --> 25:59.850
All that time you worked
at your company,

26:00.768 --> 26:05.137
you danced
the fine line between
company man and family man.

26:07.400 --> 26:09.106
I'm not much for danCing.

26:10.486 --> 26:12.147
You're over-simplifying it.

26:12.780 --> 26:14.896
I think you're
over-complicating it.

26:15.658 --> 26:17.649
Hunting them
or harboring them.

26:18.494 --> 26:23.363
To win this war for good,
it takes focus,

26:24.333 --> 26:26.870
and yours is just
a little split right now.

26:29.005 --> 26:31.371
I've read your files,
too, Mr. Danko.

26:32.717 --> 26:35.550
I've known men like you.
Is that right?

26:35.636 --> 26:39.049
Sure. Simple, unconnected,
take your work home with you,

26:39.140 --> 26:42.177
you're never off the job.
You think that
makes you perfect.

26:42.268 --> 26:45.101
Not perfect,
just better than you.

26:45.188 --> 26:48.726
These aren't terrorist
you're hunting,
they're people.

26:49.400 --> 26:51.140
They're targets.

26:51.235 --> 26:56.696
This job is about
understanding their humanity,
not their ability.

26:59.202 --> 27:01.864
But you have to be
human to do that.

27:04.207 --> 27:06.038
You're a valuable asset,

27:07.293 --> 27:12.003
but once we begin engagement,
l have to know,
are you gonna take orders,

27:13.049 --> 27:15.665
or continue undermining me
with every glance?

27:18.763 --> 27:20.424
You're the boss.

27:27.730 --> 27:29.311
(GRUNTING)

27:33.486 --> 27:36.978
MR. BENNET: (WEARILY)
Matt, don't do this.
Don't push this any further.

27:37.073 --> 27:39.985
Peter, I got another
address for you.
MR. BENNET: No.

27:40.076 --> 27:42.158
PETER: What is it?
What did you see?

27:42.245 --> 27:46.488
No. You go after this guy
and you're dead. You're
all dead, you can't undo it.

27:46.582 --> 27:48.288
This guy's in Charge.

27:48.376 --> 27:49.707
(GROANING)

27:51.045 --> 27:53.787
Don't listen to him.
This is why we came.

27:53.881 --> 27:55.712
We want to cripple them,
we want to hurt them.

27:55.842 --> 28:00.552
This is the guy.
No, Peter.
You're making a big mistake.

28:00.638 --> 28:03.095
You're unraveling things
you don't understand.

28:05.601 --> 28:06.977
(GUN COCKING)

28:08.396 --> 28:09.636
Peter!

28:13.442 --> 28:14.773
Peter!

28:21.200 --> 28:22.189
